Package game

Class Dinosaur

java.lang.Object
edu.monash.fit2099.engine.Actor
game.Dinosaur
All Implemented Interfaces:
Capable, Printable, ActorInterface
Direct Known Subclasses:
Allosaur, Brachiosaur, Pterodactyl, Stegosaur
public class Dinosaur
extends Actor
The general class for all the dinosaurs with functions of common functionality between all the dinosaur species that will be made.

  • Constructor Summary

    Constructors
    Constructor Description
    Dinosaur​(java.lang.String name, char displayChar, int hitPoints)
    Constructor for the general dinosaurs, shared by all the species of dinosaur that extend this class and will set their name, display character and hit points and will also in random with a 50-50 chance the gender of the dinosaur as a male or female.
    Dinosaur​(java.lang.String name, char displayChar, int hitPoints, java.lang.String gender)
    the admin class to create dinosaurs which create dinosaurs in the same way by setting their name, display char and hit points but unlike the three parameter constructor, it will allow direct setting of the gender of the dinosaur

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type Method Description
    Action breeding​(GameMap map)
    calls the required behaviours of the dinosaur for it to breed, the behaviour checks all the attributes of the dinosaur and whether or not the requirements for it to breed are met, and returns the action for the dinosaur to breed and if requirements not met returns null.
    Action dies​(GameMap map)
    calls the required behaviours of the dinosaur for it to die, the behaviour checks all the attributes of the dinosaur and whether or not the requirements for it to die are met, and returns the action for the dinosaur to die and if requirements not met returns null.

    called when a dinosaur drinks water and will increase the water level of the dinosaur by the amount of water it drinks
    void drinkRain()
    every time the sky rains if a dinosaur is unconscious due to thirst it can drink the rain water and come back to a water level of 10
    Action drinks​(GameMap map)
